```python
def all_ints_div_by_num(nums):
    return [num for num in nums[:1] if num % 9 == 0]
```
Note: This code assumes that the specified range is from index 0 to index 0, i.e., it will only check the first element of the list. If the range is meant to be from index 0 to the last index, you can modify the code accordingly by replacing `nums[:1]` with `nums[:len(nums)]`.
